		{"id":"text-var1-ad28","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Staff room coffee pot, blurry vending machine in back.","x":4000,"y":7780,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad28","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a coffee mug with \"World's Best Teacher\" on it.","x":4450,"y":7780,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad4","type":"text","text":"# Ad #4 — The Bench\n\nI was sitting on the park bench watching him, too tired to move.\n\nMy two-year-old son was running around, full of life, and I couldn't keep up.\n\nI’m a nurse. I spend 12 hours a day on my feet. \n\nBut when I got home, I had nothing left for my own family.\n\nI’ve felt like this since my pregnancy. \n\nI didn't recognize myself in photos. I felt disconnected from my own identity.\n\nI tried the \"discipline\" approach. I tried the \"willpower\" approach.\n\nI spent hundreds on supplements that did nothing but make me jittery.\n\nI felt like I was failing as a mom.\n\nThen a friend told me about the medical support she was getting through Elevate.\n\nShe said it wasn't about willpower. It was about biology.\n\nI did the medical review from my couch while my son napped.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and created a personalized plan.\n\nThe meds and supplies were delivered right to my doorstep.\n\nThe biggest change wasn't the scale. It was the \"food noise.\"\n\nFor the first time in years, I wasn't constantly thinking about my next meal.\n\nI felt in control. I felt like \"Sarah\" again.\n\nLast weekend, we went back to that same park.\n\nI wasn't sitting on the bench. I was the one chasing him.\n\nI stopped wasting money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow I pay $58 a week for a medical plan that actually does.\n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nCheck if you're eligible for the same support. It changed my life.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":2860,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad4","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_04/Var2/variant-1.png","x":450,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad2","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_02/Var2/variant-1.png","x":450,"y":660,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad2","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a broken zipper on a pair of navy blue scrubs.","x":450,"y":1180,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad2","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_02/Var3/variant-1.png","x":900,"y":660,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad2","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nClose-up of hands struggling to pull up a zipper on tight scrub pants.","x":900,"y":1180,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad4","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Empty park bench with a toddler’s shoe left on the seat.","x":450,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad4","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_04/Var3/variant-1.png","x":900,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad4","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nWoman sitting on a park bench, exhausted and out of breath.","x":900,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad4","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_04/Var1/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad3","type":"text","text":"# Ad #3 — The Night Shift\n\n3:45 AM is a lonely time to realize you’re stuck.\n\nI was halfway through another double shift, leaning against the nursing station.\n\nI was staring at the vending machine, thinking about a snack I didn't even want.\n\nThat was my life. Constant \"food noise\" and zero energy.\n\nI’m a 34-year-old RN. I spend my whole day taking care of others.\n\nBut I was neglecting myself. \n\nI felt like a stranger in my own body ever since my son was born.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" Physically and mentally.\n\nI tried the meal prep. I tried the expensive gym classes. \n\nBut as a nurse and a new mom, I have zero extra time.\n\nI felt like I was failing at everything.\n\nThen I heard about Elevate from a coworker. \n\nShe told me it was medical support designed for people who actually have lives.\n\nI took the quiz on my phone right there at the station.\n\nThe medical review was 100% online. No extra appointments.\n\nA licensed provider looked at my history and created a personalized plan.\n\nThey even included anti-nausea meds to make sure I could keep working.\n\nTen days in, I woke up without that usual cloud of exhaustion.\n\nI felt lighter. Not just on the scale, but in my mind.\n\nThe obsession with food just... stopped.\n\nI finally had the energy to be the mom my son deserves.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"miracle\" pills and gym fees I never used.\n\nMy program is $58 a week. $0 down to start.\n\nIf you’ve hit a biological wall, you aren't alone.\n\nMost people don't know they qualify for medical support until they check.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":1760,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad4","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Messy living room: nurse bag next to toy blocks.","x":0,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad3","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_03/Var1/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":1760,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad3","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Cold coffee cup on nursing station desk, shift list.","x":0,"y":2280,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad2","type":"text","text":"# Ad #2 — The Broken Zipper\n\nThe zipper didn't just snag. It broke.\n\nI was getting ready for my shift, reaching for my pre-pregnancy scrubs. \n\nThe ones I’ve kept in the front of my closet as a \"goal.\"\n\nI pulled them on. I held my breath. I reached for the zipper. *Snap.*\n\nI sat on the edge of my bed and cried for twenty minutes. \n\nI’m a nurse. I’m 34. I’m a mom to a beautiful toddler. \n\nBut I felt like a failure because I couldn't even zip up my own clothes.\n\nI avoid every family photo. I make excuses to stay home. \n\nI felt like I was losing my identity.\n\nI tried the extreme calorie counting. I tried the 5 AM workouts before my shift. \n\nI was exhausted. I was irritable. And the scale wouldn't move.\n\nI thought I was just destined to feel \"heavy\" for the rest of my life.\n\nThen I saw a post from a fellow nurse who found Elevate.\n\nI didn't think I could afford medical support. I thought insurance would deny me.\n\nBut Elevate is different. No insurance red tape. No waiting rooms.\n\nI did the medical review on my phone during my lunch break.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and designed a plan just for my body.\n\nThe medication and supplies arrived in a discreet box a few days later.\n\nThe first thing I noticed was the quiet. \n\nThe mental obsession with food—the \"food noise\"—just vanished.\n\nI felt in control for the first time in years.\n\nNow, I have the energy to actually play with my son after work.\n\nI’m not spending money on useless supplements anymore.\n\nMy care plan is $58 a week, and I started for $0 down.\n\nIt wasn't a lack of discipline. It was my biology.\n\nSee if you're eligible to get the support you actually need.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":660,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad3","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_03/Var2/variant-1.png","x":450,"y":1760,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad3","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Blurry vending machine lights reflected in a nurse’s station window.","x":450,"y":2280,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad2","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_02/Var1/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":660,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad2","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Stethoscope flatlay on messy kitchen counter.","x":0,"y":1180,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad1","type":"text","text":"# Ad #1 — The Mirror\n\nI didn't recognize the woman in the nursing station mirror.\n\nIt was 3:45 AM, halfway through a double shift at the hospital. \n\nI was washing my face with that harsh industrial soap, trying to wake myself up, when I caught my reflection.\n\nMy skin looked dull. My eyes were tired. But it was more than that.\n\nI looked like a stranger to myself.\n\nI’m 34. I’m a nurse. I’m a mother to a beautiful two-year-old boy. \n\nBut for the last two years, I’ve felt like I’m living in someone else’s body.\n\nThe breaking point happened three weeks ago when I tried to fit into my pre-pregnancy scrubs and the zipper snapped.\n\nI sat on the edge of my bed and cried. I felt like I was failing as a mom because I didn't even have the energy to play.\n\nI spent a fortune on \"healthy\" meal prep services that just rotted in the fridge because I was too tired to cook.\n\nI bought a gym membership that I used exactly twice. I tried every caffeine supplement on the market.\n\nNothing worked. I just felt more defeated.\n\nThen, I talked to Maria, another nurse on my shift. She always had steady energy.\n\nShe told me she’d started a medical weight loss program through Elevate.\n\nI was skeptical. I’ve seen the ads for those expensive medications that cost $1,200.\n\nBut she showed me how Elevate works. It was a 100% online medical review.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and created a personalized care plan for me. \n\nEverything was delivered discreetly to my door.\n\nAbout ten days in, that \"heavy\" feeling was just gone.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant mental loop of thinking about my next break—finally stopped.\n\nLast week, I spent the whole afternoon at the park with my son. \n\nI wasn't sitting on the bench. I was running with him.\n\nI finally feel like me again.\n\nI was wasting hundreds on quick fixes that did nothing. Now, my plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to get started for $0 down. \n\nIf you feel like you're doing everything right and nothing is changing, it might be biological.\n\nSee if you qualify today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":-440,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad1","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_01/Var1_New/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":-440,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad1","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Selfie in hospital bathroom scrubs, tired look.","x":0,"y":80,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad1","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_01/Var2_New/variant-1.png","x":450,"y":-440,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad1","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of harsh hospital soap on hands in industrial sink.","x":450,"y":80,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad17","type":"text","text":"# Ad #17 — The Grill\n\nI used to be the guy who stayed by the grill just so I wouldn't have to walk around the party.\n\nI’m 45. I’m a business owner. I’m a dad to three great kids.\n\nBut for the last few years, I’ve been hiding in plain sight.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I was worrying about my heart. I was worrying about my longevity.\n\nI tried the \"miracle\" diets. I tried the extreme gym programs that I couldn't keep up with.\n\nI spent a fortune on supplements that did nothing but make me feel nauseous.\n\nI felt like I was failing my family. I was providing for them, but I wasn't *present* with them.\n\nThen I heard about Elevate from a buddy who finally looked like himself again.\n\nHe told me it was a medical approach that bypassed the insurance red tape entirely.\n\nI did the medical review on my phone during my lunch break.\n\nIt was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and created a personalized plan.\n\nEverything arrived discreetly at my door a few days later.\n\nThe first thing I noticed was the \"food noise\" going quiet.\n\nThe constant mental obsession with snacks and meals just vanished.\n\nI felt a level of mental clarity and focus I hadn't felt in years.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. I didn't feel like I was walking through mud anymore.\n\nLast weekend, we had a family BBQ, and I wasn't just standing at the grill.\n\nI was the one organized the touch football game in the yard.\n\nI stopped wasting money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow, my medical care plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIf you’re tired of being a spectator in your own life, see if you qualify.\n\nIt’s not about willpower. It’s about getting the right medical support.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":1540,"y":6160,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad27","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_27/Var1/variant-1.png","x":4000,"y":6160,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad27","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_27/Var2/variant-1.png","x":4450,"y":6160,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad17","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_17/Var1/variant-1.png","x":2000,"y":6160,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad17","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_17/Var2/variant-1.png","x":2450,"y":6160,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad27","type":"text","text":"# Ad #27 — The Classroom Corner\n\nI finally have the energy to be the teacher my students deserve.\n\nI’m 51. I’ve been teaching high school for 25 years. I love my job.\n\nBut for the last three years, I’ve been dragging myself through the day.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I felt like menopause had stolen my spark and replaced it with exhaustion.\n\nI avoid every school photo. I stay behind my desk as much as possible.\n\nI felt like I was losing my identity. I felt like a stranger in my own body.\n\nI tried the \"hormone\" teas. I tried the extreme calorie counting. \n\nI was hungry, I was irritable, and I was defeated.\n\nI felt like a failure. I was supposed to be a leader, but I couldn't lead myself.\n\nThen I heard about Elevate from a fellow educator who looked like she’d found the fountain of youth.\n\nShe told me it was medical weight loss that actually addressed the biology of the problem.\n\nI did the online medical review from my armchair at home.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and created a personalized care plan for me.\n\nEverything was delivered discreetly to my door a few days later.\n\nThe first change wasn't the scale. It was the \"food noise.\"\n\nThe mental obsession with what I’d eat during my break just vanished.\n\nI felt in control for the first time in years.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My passion for teaching came roaring back.\n\nLast week, I was in the center of the room, leading a debate, and I felt like me again.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"quick fixes\" that did nothing.\n\nNow, my medical care plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIf you’ve hit a wall, it’s not your fault. It might be your biology.\n\nSee if you're eligible for medical support today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":3540,"y":6160,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad17","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): BBQ tongs on a grill side-table, water bottle.","x":2000,"y":6680,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad17","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a burger being flipped; focus on the tongs.","x":2450,"y":6680,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad17","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_17/Var3/variant-1.png","x":2900,"y":6160,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad17","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nHolding up an old, oversized belt showing new tighter notches.","x":2900,"y":6680,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad7","type":"text","text":"# Ad #7 — The Watch\n\nEverything I needed arrived right at my doorstep.\n\nNo doctors' offices. No waiting rooms. No awkward conversations at the pharmacy.\n\nAs a nurse and a mom, I don't have time for extra appointments.\n\nI’ve been struggling with my weight ever since my son was born two years ago.\n\nI felt like a stranger in my own body. I felt \"heavy\" every single day.\n\nI tried the supplements. I tried the gym. I tried the \"detox\" teas.\n\nNothing worked. I just felt more exhausted.\n\nI felt like I was failing my son because I didn't have the energy to play with him.\n\nThen I found Elevate.\n\nThe medical review was 100% online. It took me two minutes.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and created a personalized care plan.\n\nThey even included anti-nausea meds so I wouldn't have to miss a shift.\n\nThe box arrived discreetly, and the instructions were so easy to follow.\n\nThe \"food noise\" stopped almost immediately.\n\nI felt in control of my body again. \n\nI finally had the energy to be the mom I wanted to be.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"quick fixes\" that did nothing.\n\nNow, my professional care plan is $58 a week.\n\nI used Afterpay for $0 down to get started.\n\nMost people don't know they qualify for medical support until they check.\n\nSee if you’re eligible today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":6040,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad7","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_07/Var1/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":6040,"width":399,"height":500},
