		{"id":"img-var2-ad26","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_26/Var2/variant-1.png","x":4450,"y":5060,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad26","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a red pen circling a date on a wall calendar.","x":4450,"y":5580,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad16","type":"text","text":"# Ad #16 — The Early Morning\n\nThe \"heavy\" feeling I’ve carried for a decade finally disappeared last Tuesday.\n\nI was driving to my office at 6 AM, and for the first time in years, I didn't feel like I was dragging a weight behind me.\n\nI’m 45. I own a small business. I have a wife and three kids who depend on me.\n\nBut for the last ten years, I’ve felt like I was failing them physically.\n\nI worried about my heart. I worried about not being around to see my kids grow up.\n\nI’d tried every diet that my employees mentioned. \n\nI spent thousands on \"weight loss\" pills from the drugstore that just made me jittery and anxious.\n\nMy insurance agent had told me my health wasn't \"a priority\" for coverage.\n\nI felt like I was stuck in a body that didn't belong to me.\n\nThen I found Elevate through a buddy in my business mastermind group.\n\nHe told me it was medical weight loss without the insurance red tape.\n\nI did the medical review on my phone that night.\n\nIt was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and designed a plan just for me.\n\nEverything was delivered discreetly to my door a few days later.\n\nThe first change wasn't the scale. It was the mental clarity.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant mental obsession with food—finally stopped.\n\nI felt in control of my body for the first time since my twenties.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My focus at work has never been better.\n\nLast weekend, I spent the whole afternoon playing catch with my kids.\n\nI wasn't the dad watching from the sidelines. I was in the game.\n\nI was wasting so much money on \"quick fixes\" that did nothing.\n\nNow, I have a professional medical plan for $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIf you’ve hit a biological wall, it’s not your fault.\n\nSee if you're eligible for the support you actually need.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":1540,"y":5060,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad16","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_16/Var2/variant-1.png","x":2450,"y":5060,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad26","type":"text","text":"# Ad #26 — The Planner\n\nI’ve taught for 25 years, but I couldn't learn how to fix my own metabolism.\n\nI’m 51. I’ve always been disciplined. I’ve always been a worker.\n\nBut when menopause hit, it felt like my body had a mind of its own.\n\nThe \"incident\" was realizing I had bought a size I never thought I’d see in my closet.\n\nI sat on the floor of my bedroom and felt like a stranger to myself.\n\nI avoid every family photo. I make excuses to miss staff dinners. \n\nI felt like I was losing my identity as a teacher and as a woman.\n\nI tried Weight Watchers for the fourth time. I tried the \"detox\" shakes.\n\nI was always hungry, always tired, and always defeated.\n\nI felt like a failure. I was coaching my students to never give up, but I was ready to quit on myself.\n\nThen I read a review from another teacher who felt the exact same \"biological wall\" at 50.\n\nShe mentioned Elevate and how they provide personalized medical support.\n\nI took the quiz at my desk during my prep period.\n\nThe medical review was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and created a plan.\n\nEverything was delivered discreetly to my door a few days later.\n\nThe first results moment happened about ten days in.\n\nI was in the middle of a lecture and I realized the \"food noise\" was gone.\n\nThe mental obsession with what I’d eat for lunch had finally stopped.\n\nI felt in control for the first time in years.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My passion for teaching came back in full force.\n\nLast week, I actually stood in the front of the room with confidence.\n\nI wasn't hiding behind my desk anymore. I was leading.\n\nI was wasting so much money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIt wasn't a willpower problem. It was my biology.\n\nSee if you qualify for the support you actually need.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":3540,"y":5060,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad26","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_26/Var3/variant-1.png","x":4900,"y":5060,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad26","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nClose-up of feet stepping onto a digital bathroom scale.","x":4900,"y":5580,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad16","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_16/Var1/variant-1.png","x":2000,"y":5060,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad5","type":"text","text":"# Ad #5 — The Steering Wheel\n\nI asked Maria how she stayed so steady during our night shifts.\n\nWe were walking to our cars after a long rotation, and she looked fresh.\n\nI was exhausted, dragging my feet, and already thinking about what I’d eat when I got home.\n\nShe told me she’d finally addressed the biological side of her weight loss with Elevate.\n\nI was 34, a nurse, and a new mom. I thought I was just meant to be tired forever.\n\nI’d tried everything to lose the baby weight, but nothing stuck.\n\nI felt like I was living in a body that didn't belong to me.\n\nThe mental \"food noise\" was the worst part. It was constant.\n\nMaria told me Elevate was 100% online and didn't need insurance.\n\nI took the quiz in my car before driving home.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my medical history and designed a plan for me.\n\nEverything I needed was delivered discreetly to my house.\n\nThe transformation started with my energy levels.\n\nI didn't have those massive crashes anymore.\n\nThe obsession with food just faded away.\n\nI finally felt like I was back in the driver’s seat of my own life.\n\nI have energy for my son now. I have confidence at work again.\n\nI was spending so much on \"quick fixes.\"\n\nNow, I have a professional medical plan for $58 a week.\n\nI used Afterpay for $0 down to get started.\n\nDon't wait until you're at your breaking point. \n\nSee if you qualify for medical support today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":3960,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-ad6","type":"text","text":"# Ad #6 — The Kitchen\n\nThe \"food noise\" finally went quiet.\n\nThat's the only way I can describe it. \n\nBefore Elevate, my brain was constantly scanning for the next snack, the next break, the next meal.\n\nIt was exhausting. Especially while working 12-hour nursing shifts.\n\nI’m 34. I’m a mom. I love my life, but I hated how I felt in my body.\n\nI’d tried the meal prep. I’d tried the \"low carb\" everything. \n\nBut the mental obsession never stopped.\n\nI felt like I was failing because I didn't have enough willpower.\n\nThen I realized it wasn't a willpower problem. It was a biology problem.\n\nI found Elevate and decided to try the medical approach.\n\nThe review was 100% online and very thorough.\n\nA licensed provider looked at my history and created a personalized care plan.\n\nThe medication and supplies were delivered discreetly to my door.\n\nWithin two weeks, the constant thoughts about food just disappeared.\n\nI felt \"light\" in my head for the first time in years.\n\nI had the mental space to actually focus on my son and my patients.\n\nI stopped buying expensive \"diet\" foods that didn't work.\n\nNow, my medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to get started for $0 down.\n\nIf you’re tired of the mental battle, see if you qualify for medical support.\n\nIt's not about trying harder. It's about getting the right care.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":5060,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad6","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Prepped veggies next to a baby bib on counter.","x":0,"y":5580,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad6","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: A quiet, clean kitchen island with a single glass of water.","x":450,"y":5580,"width":400,"height":100},
