		{"id":"img-var3-ad13","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_13/Var3/variant-1.png","x":2900,"y":1760,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad13","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nFather out of breath, hands on his knees, panting in the backyard.","x":2900,"y":2280,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad15","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Business card that says \"Strategy\" resting next to a full glass.","x":2450,"y":4480,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad24","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Woman walking down school hallway, reflection in glass.","x":4000,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad24","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a thick, oversized wool cardigan on a hanger.","x":4450,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad24","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_24/Var1/variant-1.png","x":4000,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad24","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_24/Var2/variant-1.png","x":4450,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad24","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_24/Var3/variant-1.png","x":4900,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad14","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_14/Var1/variant-1.png","x":2000,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad14","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Laptop and notebook next to a half-eaten donut.","x":2000,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad14","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_14/Var2/variant-1.png","x":2450,"y":2860,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad24","type":"text","text":"# Ad #24 — The Hallway Reflection\n\nI spent three years hiding behind my desk.\n\nI’m 51. I’ve been a high school teacher for 25 years. I used to love being in the middle of the classroom.\n\nBut after menopause, I didn't recognize the woman in the mirror.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I felt like my metabolism had been replaced by a stranger's.\n\nI avoid every school event. I wear the same oversized cardigans every single day. \n\nI felt like I was losing my identity as an educator and as a woman.\n\nI tried the \"hormone teas.\" I tried the extreme calorie counting that left me too tired to grade papers.\n\nI was frustrated. I was irritable. And nothing worked.\n\nI thought I was just meant to be \"the invisible teacher\" from now on.\n\nThen I saw an ad for Elevate and decided to take the quiz.\n\nI didn't think I’d qualify for medical support. I thought it was only for people with \"major\" health issues.\n\nBut Elevate looks at the whole picture. The medical review was 100% online.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and designed a plan just for me.\n\nEverything was delivered discreetly to my house.\n\nThe biggest change was the mental space I got back.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant mental obsession with my next meal—just stopped.\n\nI felt in control of my body for the first time in a decade.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My passion for teaching came roaring back.\n\nLast week, I didn't hide behind my desk. \n\nI was in the center of the room, leading a lecture, and I felt confident.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"miracle\" pills and teas.\n\nNow, I have a professional medical plan for $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay for $0 down to start.\n\nIt wasn't a willpower problem. It was my biology.\n\nSee if you qualify for the support you actually need.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":3540,"y":2860,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-ad14","type":"text","text":"# Ad #14 — The Conference Room\n\nI was in the middle of a million-dollar pitch, but all I could think about was the donuts in the breakroom.\n\nThat’s what \"food noise\" feels like. It’s a constant mental loop that overrides everything else.\n\nI’m a 45-year-old business owner. I’m supposed to be the most focused person in the room.\n\nBut my brain was constantly scanning for the next snack, the next meal, the next distraction.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I felt like I was losing my edge.\n\nI worried about my health. I worried about being around for my wife and my three kids.\n\nI tried the \"willpower\" approach. I tried the expensive meal plans that I never had time to eat.\n\nI spent hundreds on drugstore \"weight loss\" pills that just made me irritable and anxious.\n\nI felt like I was winning at business but losing at life.\n\nThen I heard about Elevate from a buddy in my mastermind group.\n\nHe told me he’d found a medical approach that actually addressed the biology of the problem.\n\nI did the medical review on my phone between meetings.\n\nIt was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and designed a plan just for me.\n\nNo insurance agents telling me I wasn't \"at risk enough\" to qualify for help.\n\nThe medication and supplies were delivered discreetly to my door.\n\nWithin ten days, the \"food noise\" just... stopped.\n\nI felt a level of mental clarity I hadn't experienced since my twenties.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. I wasn't crashing at 3 PM anymore.\n\nLast week, I sat through a three-hour board meeting and didn't think about food once.\n\nI finally felt like I was back in control of my own mind.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"quick fixes\" that did nothing.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to get started for $0 down.\n\nIf you’re doing everything right and your brain is still fighting you, it’s not your fault.\n\nSee if you're eligible for medical support today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":1540,"y":2860,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad14","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Hand taking a notebook from a stack; blurry donuts in back.","x":2450,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad24","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nHolding up an oversized wool cardigan used to hide in.","x":4900,"y":3380,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad23","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_23/Var1/variant-1.png","x":4000,"y":1760,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad23","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Tupperware salad on breakroom table, lanyard.","x":4000,"y":2280,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad23","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Blurry box of donuts sitting on a staff room counter.","x":4450,"y":2280,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad23","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_23/Var2/variant-1.png","x":4450,"y":1760,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad13","type":"text","text":"# Ad #13 — The Baseball Glove\n\nI used to watch my kids play from the kitchen window because I didn't have the energy to join them.\n\nI’m 45. I own a small business. I work 60 hours a week.\n\nI told myself I was \"too busy\" to be healthy. But the truth was, I was just exhausted.\n\nI felt \"heavy\" every single morning. I felt like a spectator in my own family.\n\nI worried about my heart. I worried about not being there to see my kids grow up.\n\nI tried the \"miracle\" diets. I tried the 5 AM workouts that lasted three days before I quit.\n\nI spent a fortune on supplements that did nothing but collect dust in the pantry.\n\nI felt like a failure as a dad. I was providing for them, but I wasn't *with* them.\n\nThen a friend from my business group mentioned Elevate.\n\nHe told me it was medical weight loss without the insurance red tape.\n\nI was skeptical until I saw his transformation. \n\nI did the online medical review from my desk during a lunch break.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and created a personalized care plan for me.\n\nThe medication and supplies arrived discreetly at my office.\n\nThe first change wasn't the scale. It was the \"food noise.\"\n\nThe constant mental obsession with what I was going to eat next just vanished.\n\nI felt in control of my body for the first time in years.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My mental clarity at work skyrocketed.\n\nLast weekend, I didn't watch from the window. \n\nI was out in the yard playing catch for two hours. And I didn't want to stop.\n\nI was wasting so much money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow, I have a medical care plan that costs me $58 a week.\n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIt wasn't a willpower problem. It was my biology.\n\nSee if you're eligible for the support that actually works.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":1540,"y":1760,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad13","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_13/Var1/variant-1.png","x":2000,"y":1760,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad13","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Worn baseball glove on a lawn chair, backyard view.","x":2000,"y":2280,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad20","type":"text","text":"# Ad #20 — The Mirror\n\nI finally recognize the man in the mirror again.\n\nI’m 45. I’m a business owner. For the last ten years, I’ve felt like a stranger was living in my body.\n\nI was successful at work, but I felt like a failure at home.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I was worrying about my heart. I was worrying about not being around for my three kids.\n\nI tried the fad diets. I tried the extreme gym programs. \n\nI spent a fortune on supplements that did nothing but make me feel irritable.\n\nMy insurance agent had told me my health wasn't \"a priority\" for coverage.\n\nI felt like I was losing my edge and my identity.\n\nThen I found Elevate through a buddy who finally looked like his old self again.\n\nHe told me it was medical weight loss without the insurance red tape.\n\nI took the quiz on my phone that night. \n\nThe medical review was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and created a plan.\n\nEverything arrived discreetly at my door a few days later.\n\nThe first results moment happened within the first week.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant mental obsession with my next meal—just vanished.\n\nI felt a mental clarity and focus I hadn't felt in a decade.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My confidence at work has never been higher.\n\nLast weekend, I spent three hours playing catch with my kids and didn't need a single break.\n\nI was wasting so much money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan for $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to get started for $0 down.\n\nIf you’re ready to feel like yourself again, it’s not about willpower.\n\nSee if you're eligible for medical support today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":1540,"y":9460,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad20","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_20/Var1/variant-1.png","x":2000,"y":9460,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad20","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Reflection of hands adjusting a silk tie in mirror.","x":2000,"y":9980,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad20","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_20/Var2/variant-1.png","x":2450,"y":9460,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad20","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a wedding ring on a hand smoothing a white shirt.","x":2450,"y":9980,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad20","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_20/Var3/variant-1.png","x":2900,"y":9460,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad20","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nHolding up an old pair of suit pants that are now sizes too big.","x":2900,"y":9980,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad18","type":"text","text":"# Ad #18 — The Receipt\n\nI realized I was spending more on entertaining clients than I was on my own longevity.\n\nI’m 45. I own a small business. I’m used to making smart investments.\n\nBut for a long time, I was ignoring the most important asset I have: my health.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I was worrying about my heart. I was worrying about being there for my three kids.\n\nI’d tried the fad diets. I’d spent thousands on \"weight loss\" pills from the drugstore.\n\nNothing worked. I just felt more exhausted and more defeated.\n\nMy insurance agent had told me my health wasn't \"a priority\" for coverage.\n\nI felt like I was winning at work but losing at everything that actually mattered.\n\nThen I found Elevate through a buddy in my business group.\n\nHe told me it was medical weight loss without the insurance red tape or the waiting rooms.\n\nI took the quiz on my phone while waiting for a client to arrive.\n\nThe medical review was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and created a plan.\n\nEverything I needed was delivered discreetly to my house.\n\nThe transformation started with the mental clarity.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant mental obsession with my next meal—just stopped.\n\nI felt in control of my body for the first time in years.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My energy at the office was higher than it had been in a decade.\n\nLast weekend, I played catch with my kids for three hours and didn't need a break.\n\nI was wasting so much money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan for $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIf you’re ready to invest in your health, see if you qualify today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":1540,"y":7260,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad19","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_19/Var1_Text/variant-1.png","x":2000,"y":8360,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad19","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_19/Var2/variant-1.png","x":2450,"y":8360,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad18","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_18/Var1/variant-1.png","x":2000,"y":7260,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad18","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/David_Ad_18/Var2/variant-1.png","x":2450,"y":7260,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad19","type":"text","text":"# Ad #19 — The Desk\n\nNo insurance red tape. No waiting rooms. Just a path forward.\n\nI’m 45. I’m a small business owner. I don’t have time for doctors’ waiting rooms or insurance agents.\n\nFor years, I’ve felt like my health was holding me back.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I was worrying about my heart. I was worrying about my future with my three kids.\n\nI tried the \"willpower\" approach. I tried the expensive meal plans that were a hassle to maintain.\n\nI spent a fortune on supplements that did nothing but make me feel anxious.\n\nI felt like a failure because I couldn't even fix my own body.\n\nThen I heard about Elevate and the \"no insurance\" model.\n\nI did the medical review on my phone during my lunch break.\n\nIt was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and designed a plan just for me.\n\nEverything was delivered to my house discreetly.\n\nWithin ten days, the \"food noise\" just stopped.\n\nThe constant mental obsession with food was replaced by mental clarity.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. I had more focus at the office than I’d had in years.\n\nLast weekend, I was out in the yard playing catch with my kids until dark.\n\nI wasn't the dad sitting on the porch. I was the one leading the game.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"quick fixes\" that did nothing.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nDon't let the healthcare system dictate your health.\n\nSee if you're eligible for medical support today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":1540,"y":8360,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad19","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Clean home office desk, monitor showing Elevate site.","x":2000,"y":8880,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad19","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a finger clicking \"Check Eligibility\" on a mouse.","x":2450,"y":8880,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad18","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a receipt with a high total, next to a car key fob.","x":2450,"y":7780,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad9","type":"text","text":"# Ad #9 — The Old Photo\n\nI thought medical weight loss was only for the \"lucky\" few.\n\nI’m a 34-year-old nurse. I’ve been struggling with my weight since my son was born.\n\nI felt like I was doing everything right, but the scale wouldn't budge.\n\nI looked at old photos of myself and didn't even recognize that girl.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" Disconnected. Defeated.\n\nI tried the extreme diets. I tried the expensive trainers. \n\nI spent hundreds on supplements that did nothing but give me a headache.\n\nI felt like I was failing my family because I had zero energy to be present.\n\nThen a coworker told me about Elevate.\n\nI didn't think my insurance would cover it. I didn't think I’d qualify.\n\nBut Elevate is different. It’s a 100% online medical review.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and created a personalized plan.\n\nNo insurance needed. No waiting rooms.\n\nEverything was delivered discreetly to my house.\n\nThe \"food noise\" stopped within the first week.\n\nI felt in control for the first time in years.\n\nI finally feel like that girl in the old photos again.\n\nI stopped wasting money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow, my medical plan is $58 a week. $0 down to get started.\n\nIf you’ve hit a wall, it might not be your fault. It might be your biology.\n\nTake the quiz. See if you're eligible for support.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":8240,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"text-ad10","type":"text","text":"# Ad #10 — The Hallway\n\nI spend my whole life taking care of everyone else.\n\nAs a 34-year-old RN and a new mom, my time is never my own.\n\nFor two years, I’ve felt like I was drowning.\n\nI was exhausted. I was \"heavy.\" I was constantly thinking about food.\n\nI tried the meal prep. I tried the gym. I tried the willpower.\n\nNothing worked. I just felt more defeated and more tired.\n\nI felt like I was failing at being a mom because I didn't have the energy to play.\n\nThen I decided to finally prioritize my own health with Elevate.\n\nI did the medical review on my phone during a break.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and designed a plan for me.\n\nEverything was delivered to my house. Discreet and simple.\n\nThe mental clarity was the first thing I noticed.\n\nThe \"food noise\" just stopped. I felt in control.\n\nI finally have the energy to be the mom my son deserves.\n\nI’m not spending money on useless \"fixes\" anymore.\n\nMy professional medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to get started for $0 down.\n\nIf you’re doing everything right and it’s still not working, it’s not your fault.\n\nMost people don't know they qualify for medical support until they check.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":9340,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad10","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_10/Var1/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":9340,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad10","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_10/Var2/variant-1.png","x":450,"y":9340,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad10","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Long, empty hospital hallway at night, soft light.","x":0,"y":9860,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad10","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a nurse’s ID badge resting on a bedside table.","x":450,"y":9860,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad18","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Leather wallet and car keys on marble table, receipt.","x":2000,"y":7780,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad8","type":"text","text":"# Ad #8 — The Shoes\n\nI finally feel like \"Sarah\" again.\n\nNot just \"Mom.\" Not just \"Nurse.\" \n\nFor two years, I felt like a stranger was living in my body.\n\nI avoided every photo. I felt \"heavy\" all the time. \n\nI tried every diet on the market, but nothing stuck.\n\nI’m 34. I’m an RN. I take care of people every day. \n\nBut I couldn't figure out how to take care of myself.\n\nI felt like I was failing as a mom because I had zero energy.\n\nThen I found the medical support I needed through Elevate.\n\nI did the medical review on my phone while my son was napping.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my history and designed a plan just for me.\n\nEverything was delivered to my house in a discreet box.\n\nThe biggest change was the mental clarity.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant thoughts about snacks and meals—just stopped.\n\nI felt in control for the first time since my pregnancy.\n\nNow, when I get home from a shift, I still have energy for my son.\n\nI’m not spending money on useless supplements or gym fees anymore.\n\nMy care plan is $58 a week. I started for $0 down with Afterpay.\n\nIt wasn't a willpower problem. It was a biological one.\n\nSee if you're eligible for medical support. It changed everything for me.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":-460,"y":7140,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad9","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_09/Var1/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":8240,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad9","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_09/Var2/variant-1.png","x":450,"y":8240,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad8","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_08/Var1/variant-1.png","x":0,"y":7140,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad8","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_08/Var2/variant-1.png","x":450,"y":7140,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad8","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Nursing clogs by the door next to a diaper bag.","x":0,"y":7660,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad8","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of hands tying new, smaller sneakers.","x":450,"y":7660,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad9","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Face in profile looking at a blurred old phone photo.","x":0,"y":8760,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad9","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: A physical polaroid of \"Sarah\" on a fridge, slightly faded.","x":450,"y":8760,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad8","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Sarah_Ad_08/Var3/variant-1.png","x":900,"y":7140,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad8","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nHolding up an old pair of scrub pants that are several sizes too big.","x":900,"y":7660,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad29","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_29/Var2/variant-1.png","x":4450,"y":8360,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad29","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a hand lifting a heavy leather bag strap.","x":4450,"y":8880,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"img-var3-ad29","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_29/Var3/variant-1.png","x":4900,"y":8360,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var3-ad29","type":"text","text":"**Variation 3: Weight Loss Cue**\\nWoman tightening a belt to a newly made, much smaller notch.","x":4900,"y":8880,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad30","type":"text","text":"# Ad #30 — The Mirror Smile\n\nI finally recognize the woman in the mirror again.\n\nI’m 51. I’ve been a high school teacher for 25 years. For the last three years, I’ve felt like a stranger was living in my body.\n\nI was successful in the classroom, but I felt like a failure everywhere else.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I was worrying about my metabolism. I was worrying about my identity.\n\nI tried the fad diets. I tried the extreme gym programs. \n\nI spent a fortune on supplements that did nothing but make me feel irritable.\n\nI felt like I was losing my edge and my spark.\n\nThen I found Elevate through another teacher who finally looked like her old self again.\n\nShe told me it was medical weight loss that addressed the biology of the problem.\n\nI took the quiz on my phone that night. \n\nThe medical review was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and created a plan.\n\nEverything arrived discreetly at my door a few days later.\n\nThe first results moment happened within the first week.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant mental obsession with my next meal—just vanished.\n\nI felt a mental clarity and focus I hadn't felt in a decade.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My energy at school stayed steady all day long.\n\nLast week, I stood in the front of the classroom and I felt confident.\n\nI wasn't hiding behind my desk anymore. I was leading.\n\nI was wasting so much money on things that didn't work.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay for $0 down to start.\n\nIf you’re ready to feel like yourself again, it’s not about willpower.\n\nSee if you're eligible for medical support today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":3540,"y":9460,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad30","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_30/Var1/variant-1.png","x":4000,"y":9460,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"img-var2-ad30","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_30/Var2/variant-1.png","x":4450,"y":9460,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-ad29","type":"text","text":"# Ad #29 — The School Bag\n\nI spend my whole life teaching others how to succeed.\n\nI’m 51. I’ve been a high school teacher for 25 years. I’m a professional.\n\nBut for three years, I felt like a failure in my own skin.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I felt like my metabolism had been replaced by someone else's.\n\nI avoid every school photo. I stay behind my desk as much as possible. \n\nI felt like I was losing my identity as an educator and as a woman.\n\nI tried the \"hormone\" teas. I tried the extreme calorie counting that left me too tired to grade papers.\n\nI was frustrated. I was irritable. And nothing worked.\n\nI thought I was just meant to be \"the tired teacher\" from now on.\n\nThen I saw an ad for Elevate and decided to take the quiz.\n\nI didn't think I’d qualify for medical support. I thought it was only for people with \"major\" health issues.\n\nBut Elevate looks at the whole picture. The medical review was 100% online.\n\nA licensed provider reviewed my medical history and designed a plan just for me.\n\nEverything was delivered discreetly to my door a few days later.\n\nThe biggest change was the mental clarity.\n\nThe \"food noise\"—the constant mental obsession with my next meal—just stopped.\n\nI felt in control for the first time in years.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My passion for teaching came roaring back.\n\nLast week, I was in the center of the room, leading a lecture, and I felt like me again.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"quick fixes\" that did nothing.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIt wasn't a willpower problem. It was my biology.\n\nSee if you're eligible for medical support today.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":3540,"y":8360,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad29","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_29/Var1/variant-1.png","x":4000,"y":8360,"width":399,"height":500},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad29","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Heavy school bag on wooden floor, papers peeking out.","x":4000,"y":8880,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var1-ad30","type":"text","text":"**Variation 1**\nPersona Life (Native): Reflection of woman adjusting scarf with a small smile.","x":4000,"y":9980,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-var2-ad30","type":"text","text":"**Variation 2**\nMessage-Direct: Close-up of a bright, colorful scarf being knotted at the neck.","x":4450,"y":9980,"width":400,"height":100},
		{"id":"text-ad28","type":"text","text":"# Ad #28 — The Staff Room\n\nThe donuts in the staff room used to haunt me all day.\n\nThat’s what \"food noise\" feels like. It’s a constant mental loop that overrides your focus.\n\nI’m 51. I’ve been a high school teacher for 25 years. I’m supposed to be the one in charge.\n\nBut for three years, my brain was constantly scanning for the next snack, the next break.\n\nI felt \"heavy.\" I felt like menopause had rewritten my metabolism and I didn't have the password.\n\nI’d tried everything. The points, the shakes, the extreme fasting.\n\nI was always hungry, always tired, and always defeated.\n\nI felt like a failure. I was teaching my students about history, but I felt like I was stuck in my own past.\n\nThen I read a review from another teacher who found the medical support she needed with Elevate.\n\nShe said it wasn't about \"trying harder.\" It was about addressing the biological shift.\n\nI took the quiz on my phone during a hallway transition.\n\nThe medical review was 100% online. A licensed provider reviewed my history and created a plan.\n\nNo insurance red tape. No pharmacy counters.\n\nEverything arrived discreetly at my door a few days later.\n\nWithin ten days, the \"food noise\" just... stopped.\n\nI felt a level of mental clarity I hadn't experienced since my thirties.\n\nI felt \"lighter\" on my feet. My energy at school stayed steady all day.\n\nLast week, I sat through a two-hour staff meeting and didn't think about food once.\n\nI finally felt like I was back in control of my own mind.\n\nI stopped wasting money on \"quick fixes\" that did nothing.\n\nNow, my professional medical plan is $58 a week. \n\nI used Afterpay to start for $0 down.\n\nIf you’re doing everything right and your brain is still fighting you, see if you qualify.\n\nIt’s not about willpower. It’s about getting the right care.\n\n[Link: See if you qualify]","x":3540,"y":7260,"width":400,"height":880},
		{"id":"img-var1-ad28","type":"file","file":"Elevate/00 Assets/T003/Maria_Ad_28/Var1/variant-1.png","x":4000,"y":7260,"width":399,"height":500},
